Slightly overcast- the temperature is 80 degrees F- southwest wind at 8-14 mph.
Algae blooms- slight breeze from southwest- clear sky- sunny- and the air temperature is 77 degrees F.
Algae and weed bloom apparent- lots of particles in the water- clear sky- temperature is 80 degrees F- sunny- and no wind.
Overcast- light winds- slight chop- some particles in water though fewer than previous week- and the temperature is 80 degrees F.
Southwest wind at 15 mph- 5-1" waves- partly cloudy- and the temperature is 70 degrees F.
Three days of hot weather- first mid-week test- light boat traffic for 3 days- rain two days (prior water clarity improving)- and the temperature is 84 degrees F.
Clear- light waves- and the temperature is 78 degrees F.
Continued hot last week- brief rain on 7/24/1987- algae bloom starting again- floating chunks of algae- weed growth very heavy- and this is the lowest lake level in 2 years.
Heat wave continues- water appearing clearer- low boat traffic- partly cloudy- no wind- no rain in over a week- 86 F.
Lake level's high was 8.06 and low was 7.56- 4" of rain fell during previous week- low boat traffic- clear- air 68 F.
Sunny- 72 F- light winds 5-10 mph from s- low boat traffic.
SE wind at 5 mph- clear- more particles in the water than last week- 78 F- increasing boat traffic.
More particles in the water- apparently greener- S winds at 5-10 mph- clear skies- rain previous night.
Clear sky- air temp. 60 F- water looks greener- weather causing lake traffic to drop off.
Clear skies- air temp. 29 F- fewer particles in the water- dam will be pulled on October 15 so lake level will drop for the winter.  Last test.
Ice-out 2nd weekend of March- high particle count- weeds already grown to top of water- spring lake level high -8.30/low 7.67- clear- 50 F.
Weed growth impairing enjoyment- 85-90 F- S wind 10 mph- heavy boat traffic.
Low boat traffic- weed growth high- calm- clear
High winds cleared up lake- no rain- worse algae than last year
No rain- 76-79 F- S wind 10 mph- boat traffic medium/lt.- weeds a problem
Dry- weed growth very heavy- boat traffic not as bad as other years.
Very green- no rain - weeds overgrown- tough to get to gauge
Lake down 1.5" despite 1" rain - cannot reach gauge.
Hot- no rain- lake 16" below normal- weeds appearing.
Rain 8/8- around shore water clearer than past- slight. algae bloom in s. end of lake
Rain on 8/14- lake up 2-3"- 12-14" lower than last years. lowest
Weeds excessive- interfering wi/ pleasure boating- clarity improving.
Weed problem worse- lake still dropping every week.
S/southwest wind 10-20 miles per hour- 70-75 F- last reading
Algae bloom starting- water almost out of creek where staff gauge is
Noticeable algae- silver dollar to fist sized
White specks in water and highly visible algae- wind 8-10 mph
Lt. NE winds 5 mph- 82 F- overcast.
Hazy- overcast- NE wind 7-12 mph- rained all day 7/30- level on 7/29 was 6.92
Rain this week but no change in lake level
Weeds not as much of a problem this year
Water seems cloudy- construction run- off N end of lake.
Very small particles noticeable in water
Clear- 73 F- N wind 5-7 mph- algae bloom- esp. @ S end- water very clear otherwise
High winds all weekend- choppy- difficult reading
S wind 8-15 mph- 75 F- boats not digging up bottom- carp noticeable in N end
Green slimeballs floating and on beaches
Water very green- heavy weekend and holiday boat traffic

High winds past 3 days- 20-50 mph; calm- overcast today- 70 high temperature- algae bloom happened- very minor- three days ago.  Lake had green balls of slime one week ago during the hot weather. 1/10th of 1 inch from 7/14-7/15- no rain for last 10 days.
Water green around shore- bottom water sulfur smelling
Weeds not as much of a problem this year as past
Floating algae becoming apparent @ N end 30-40' out from shore.  Calm- hazy- and overcast.  3" of rain from 7/16-8/11.  Monitor with George Wundsam during chemistry.
Very heavy storm after- level went up to 8.12'
Clear- lt. wind- 78 F- heavy boat traffic Friday and sat. (8/30-9/1)
Water greener than rest of year- last week hot- heavy boat traffic stirs up lake.
Wind 20 mph- no time entered in data- assumed noon.

10 mph wind- lake had blue/green color- nothing else unusual.  Took secchi sample on 9/19 at same location 7' reading- 20 mph wind- green color and 7.7 lake level. 6 3/10" of rain from 8/12-9/30.  Monitor with George Wundsam.
Wind 15+ mph- all else is normal.  4.4" of rain from 10/1-10/29.  Lake being lowered for winter.  Monitored with George Wundsam.
Hot- no rain for 2 weeks- heavy boat traffic last two weekends- high winds from the south.
Water level down 2' since spring - dry- clear calm- 85 F.
Cloudy- calm- no algae bloom that I could see.  Rain gauge reading from 8/31-10/3 is 4.35 inches.
Algae bloom this morning is noticeable at the shore on south end and out in the middle also.  Water smells fishy.- no time entered in data- assumed noon.
Beautiful sunny day- 65 F- no ice- no algae bloom- wind is north at 10-15 mph.  The rain gauge reading from 9/31-10/5 is 5.1 inches.
Sunny with slight haze- temp 72 F.  Monitored with the Mayers.
Lake very high- samples were taken Monday after very heavy weekend of boating.  Monitored with the Mayers.
Lake is calm- no evidence of any problems.  Monitored with the Mayers and Stormy Grumbeck.
48 degrees air temp.  Monitored with the Mayers and stormy Grumbeck.
Several algal blooms in the last month
Lake has been very cloudy even in March when I put my boat in- Department of Natural Resources dam- carp are the cause- weed growth not like in the past- very sparse
Still silty- water cloudy- weed growth is better- boat survey taken 7/15/94- 184 power boats out anchor or docked at all times on the lake
Very windy- several large milfoil patches with above water growth
Surface algal blooms- obvious beaver activity.  Lake level is 45'- 9" higher than normal
Water finally cleared up nicely- this- 10 years ago was the way it always was- increased numbers of zebra mussels- especially on the rocks.
No algae blooms yet- zebra mussels can be seen in shallow water.
Slight algal bloom- zebra mussels visible on hard surfaces in shallow water.  Water visibly clearer than this time last year.

Clear water clarity from last test (6/4) - has gone south- clarity impaired by algal bloom caused by warming water with result of suspended green matter in water giving murky green appearance - increased numbers of zebra mussels noted.
Foamy patches of suds exist as they have all summer.
Beautiful spring day. water clear- no algae.
temp. probe not functioning - so no profile.
